AB  - A path-integral Monte Carlo quantum annealing (QA) scheme for the symmetric traveling-salesman problem (TSP), based on a highly constrained Ising-like representation, was proposed. Its performance were compared against standard thermal simulated annealing. It was shown that the QA scheme, even with a drastically simple form of kinetic energy, appears definitely superior to the classical one, when tested on a 1002-city instance of the standard TSPLIB. The quantum coupling, a real positive function depending, in principle, on the links, as well as, in the annealing problem, on time was also discussed.
